There are two ways to post SIS import data - either via anmultipart/form-data form-field-style attachment, or via a non-multipart rawnpost request.nn&#39;attachment&#39; is required for multipart/form-data style posts.nAssumed to be SIS data from a file upload form field namedn&#39;attachment&#39;.nnExamples:nncurl -F attachment=@&lt;filename&gt; -H &quot;Authorization: Bearer &lt;token&gt;&quot; 
    &#39;https://&lt;canvas&gt;/api/v1/accounts/&lt;account_id&gt;/sis_imports.json?import_type=instructure_csv&#39;nnIf you decide to do a raw post, you can skip the &#39;attachment&#39;nargument, but you will then be required to provide a suitable Content-Typenheader. You are encouraged to also provide the &#39;extension&#39;nargument.nnExamples:nncurl -H &#39;Content-Type: application/octet-stream&#39; --data-binary @&lt;filename&gt;.zip 
    -H &quot;Authorization: Bearer &lt;token&gt;&quot; 
    &#39;https://&lt;canvas&gt;/api/v1/accounts/&lt;account_id&gt;/sis_imports.json?import_type=instructure_csv&amp;extension=zip&#39;nncurl -H &#39;Content-Type: application/zip&#39; --data-binary @&lt;filename&gt;.zip 
    -H &quot;Authorization: Bearer &lt;token&gt;&quot; 
    &#39;https://&lt;canvas&gt;/api/v1/accounts/&lt;account_id&gt;/sis_imports.json?import_type=instructure_csv&#39;nncurl -H &#39;Content-Type: text/csv&#39; --data-binary @&lt;filename&gt;.csv 
    -H &quot;Authorization: Bearer &lt;token&gt;&quot; 
    &#39;https://&lt;canvas&gt;/api/v1/accounts/&lt;account_id&gt;/sis_imports.json?import_type=instructure_csv&#39;nncurl -H &#39;Content-Type: text/csv&#39; --data-binary @&lt;filename&gt;.csv 
    -H &quot;Authorization: Bearer &lt;token&gt;&quot; 
    &#39;https://&lt;canvas&gt;/api/v1/accounts/&lt;account_id&gt;/sis_imports.json?import_type=instructure_csv&amp;batch_mode=1&amp;batch_mode_term_id=15&#39;
